<doc>
  <member name="D3D10_CLEAR_FLAG">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the parts of the depth stencil to clear. Usually used with <see cref="ID3D10Device.ClearDepthStencilView" />.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>These flags can be bitwise ORed together.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-reference-d3d10-core-enums">Core Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_CLEAR_FLAG.D3D10_CLEAR_DEPTH">
    <summary>
      <para>Clear the depth buffer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_CLEAR_FLAG.D3D10_CLEAR_STENCIL">
    <summary>
      <para>Clear the stencil buffer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>